  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The Cor-Knot® device is an automated knotting system for valve sutures and prosthetic rings
      used for more than a year during valve replacements and annuloplasties in cardiac surgery. It
      reduces the time spent knotting the threads fixing the prosthesis and thus reduces aortic
      clamping and extracorporeal circulation times. The originality of the project is based on the
      absence of national multi-rate data collection on the effectiveness and safety of the
      Cor-Knot® knotting device.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
